 | accessdate = 2007-07-09
 | doi = 10.1097/QAI.0b013e31815b834d
}}
</ref>

Lagarde (2003) stated that "More than 70% of the non-circumcised men (NCM) stated that they would want to be circumcised if MC were proved to protect against sexually transmitted diseases (STD)." Lagarde cautioned that "Our results strongly suggest that interventions including MC should carefully address the false sense of security that it may provide."<ref>{{cite journal
